<DocsLayout title="Smart Inbox" description="LeadEcho's three-tier smart inbox — filtering, searching, and managing incoming social mentions.">
  <h1>Smart Inbox</h1>

  <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
    The Smart Inbox is the primary interface for reviewing AI-scored social mentions.
    It organizes all incoming posts into three tiers based on relevance score and intent,
    with full-text search, platform filters, and status tracking.
  </p>

  <h2>Three Tiers</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Tier</th>
        <th>Score</th>
        <th>Intent</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Leads Ready</strong></td>
        <td>≥ 7.0</td>
        <td>buy_signal, recommendation_ask, complaint</td>
        <td>High-priority. These people need a response today.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Worth Watching</strong></td>
        <td>4.0 – 6.9</td>
        <td>Any</td>
        <td>Moderate interest. Monitor for follow-up activity.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Informational</strong></td>
        <td>&lt; 4.0</td>
        <td>general, comparison</td>
        <td>Low intent. Useful for market awareness.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Mention Statuses</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Status</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>new</code></td>
        <td>Just arrived, not yet reviewed</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>reviewed</code></td>
        <td>Viewed by a team member</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>replied</code></td>
        <td>Reply drafted or posted</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>archived</code></td>
        <td>Dismissed, hidden from active view</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>spam</code></td>
        <td>Marked as false positive</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Filtering and Search</h2>

  <p>The inbox supports the following filter dimensions:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Platform</strong> — Reddit, Twitter, LinkedIn, Dev.to, Lobsters, IndieHackers, HN</li>
    <li><strong>Intent</strong> — buy_signal, recommendation_ask, complaint, comparison, general</li>
    <li><strong>Relevance score</strong> — minimum score threshold slider</li>
    <li><strong>Status</strong> — new, reviewed, replied, archived, spam</li>
    <li><strong>Full-text search</strong> — PostgreSQL GIN index on content + author</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Performance Indexes</h2>

  <p>
    The mentions table has specialized indexes for inbox queries:
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Index Type</th>
        <th>Columns</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Partial B-tree</td>
        <td><code>relevance_score, status</code></td>
        <td>Fast "high-intent new" queries (score ≥ 7.0 AND status = new)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>GIN</td>
        <td><code>to_tsvector(content)</code></td>
        <td>Full-text search across all mention content</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>B-tree</td>
        <td><code>workspace_id, platform, created_at DESC</code></td>
        <td>Workspace-scoped platform-filtered timeline queries</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>API — List Mentions</h2>

  <pre><code>GET /api/v1/mentions
Authorization: Bearer &lt;jwt&gt;

# Query parameters:
# platform=reddit          — filter by platform
# intent=buy_signal        — filter by intent
# status=new               — filter by status
# min_score=7.0            — minimum relevance score
# q=project+management     — full-text search
# limit=20                 — page size (default 20, max 100)
# offset=0                 — pagination offset</code></pre>

  <h3>Response</h3>

  <pre><code>&#123;
  "mentions": [
    &#123;
      "id": "men_01hx...",
      "platform": "reddit",
      "author": "u/devfounder",
      "content": "We're drowning in client management...",
      "url": "https://reddit.com/r/...",
      "relevance_score": 8.5,
      "intent": "buy_signal",
      "conversion_probability": 0.82,
      "status": "new",
      "created_at": "2025-03-01T10:00:00Z"
    &#125;
  ],
  "total": 142,
  "page": 1,
  "limit": 20
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Bulk Status Updates</h2>

  <pre><code>PATCH /api/v1/mentions/&#123;id&#125;
Authorization: Bearer &lt;jwt&gt;
Content-Type: application/json

&#123;
  "status": "archived"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Tier Counts</h2>

  <p>Get counts for each inbox tier for badge display:</p>

  <pre><code>GET /api/v1/mentions/tier-counts
Authorization: Bearer &lt;jwt&gt;

# Response:
&#123;
  "leads_ready": 14,
  "worth_watching": 67,
  "informational": 203
&#125;</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
